{{orphan|date=May 2010}}

'''Carl Eric Stålberg''' (born 1951) is a [[Sweden|Swedish]] businessman and the current [[Board of Directors|Chairman]] of [[Swedbank]]. He graduated with a degree in [[business]] and [[economics]]. He entered the Board of the bank in 2001 and became its chairman in 2003. He also serves on the Board of the [[Norway|Norwegian]] [[savings bank]] [[Sparebank 1]].<ref name=CV>{{cite news |first= |last= |authorlink= |coauthors= |title=Stalberg CV  |url=http://www.swedbank.com/about-swedbank/corporate-governance/the-board-of-directors/photos-and-cv/index.htm|work=[[Swedbank Web site]] |accessdate=2009-08-21 }}</ref>

Apart from his involvement in business, he is the President of the [[Swedish Skiing Federation]] and Vice President of the [[International Ski Federation]]. Stålberg is also a member of the [[Swedish Olympic Committee]].{{Citation needed|reason=dateMay 2010|date=May 2010}}

He is also the chairman of [[Sweden-Japan Foundation]].{{Citation needed|reason=dateMay 2010|date=May 2010}}

