{{Infobox person |name = Louis Delaunay Belleville |image = Exposition universelle de 1900 - portraits des commissaires généraux-Delaunay-Belleville.jpg |image_size = 200px |caption = |birth_name = |birth_date = {{birth date|df=yes|1843|11|20}} |birth_place = [[Corbeil, Marne|Corbeil]], France |death_date = {{death date and age|df=yes|1912|02|10|1843|11|20}} |death_place = [[Cannes]], France |death_cause = |resting_place = |resting_place_coordinates = |residence = |nationality = French |other_names = Louis Marie Gabriel Delaunay |known_for = |education = |employer = |occupation = [[Business]] |home_town = [[Paris]], France |title = engineer |salary = |networth = |height = |weight = |term = |predecessor = Julien Belleville |successor = |party = |boards = |religion = |spouse = Marie Anne Elisabeth Belleville |partner = |children = Robert Delaunay Belleville (1870) and Pierre Delaunay Belleville (1872) |parents = |relatives = |signature = |website = |footnotes = owner of Delaunay-Belleville & C. firm producing boilers for ships and steam-locomotive in Saint Denis sur Seine, France |awards = [[File:Red ribbon bar - general use.svg|left|25px]][[Légion d'honneur|Legion of Honor]], [[File:ESP Charles III Order GC.svg|left|25px]] Cross of [[Order of Charles III]], [[File:Cruz del Mérito Naval con distintivo blanco.png|left|25px]][[Crosses of Naval Merit]] }} [[Image:1901-06-07-Delaunay-Belleville-&-C.ia-Saint-denis-sur-Seine-maquinario.jpg|270px|right]]
'''Louis Delaunay-Belleville''' (November 20, 1843, [[Corbeil, Marne|Corbeil]] - February 10, 1912, [[Cannes]]) was a French engineer.
==Personal life== Educated at [[Sainte-Barbe, Vosges|St. Barbe]] and the École Polytechnique, he entered the Naval Engineering School in 1864 and in 1867 left to join the Belleville works at [[Saint-Denis, Seine-Saint-Denis|St. Denis]], near [[Paris]].
He married Marie Anne Elisabeth Belleville daughter of Julien Belleville (1823-1896) and he became a partner and finally head of the firm which produced the well-known Belleville [[boiler]]s, and later the [[Delaunay-Belleville]] automobile.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gw.geneanet.org/garric?lang=it&n=delaunay+belleville&p=louis|title=Généalogies Delaunay|accessdate=October 28, 2017|language=fr}}</ref> In 1884 he changes your surname to Delaunay-Belleville.
==Encharges== * President of the Paris Chamber of Commerce from 1890 to 1909 * Régent of Banque of France * Directeur Général [[Exposition Universelle (1900)|Exposition Universelle de Paris (1900)]].
==Books== * Du régime commercial des ports de navigation intérieure en France * Lois et règlements concernant les appareils à vapeur, en Europe et aux États-Unis d'Amérique
==Honours== * He was conferred in Spain [[Crosses of Naval Merit|Cross of Naval Merit]] in 11.4.1899 <ref>La Epoca, Madrid, 4.11.1899 pag.3</ref> * He was conferred the Grand Officier de la Légion d'honneur in 12.4.1900. * He was conferred in Spain Cross of [[Order of Charles III]] in 25.10.1900 <ref>Guia Oficial de España 1910 pag.157</ref>
