'''Rickard Ericsson''', is a [[Swedish people|Swedish]] [[entrepreneur]], known as the [[Entrepreneur|founder]] of an early [[social networking website]], [[LunarStorm]].<ref>[http://hn.se/nyheter/varberg/1.740640-nar-lunarstorm-var-internet ''När Lunarstorm var internet''], [[Hallands Nyheter]] 2010-02-21 {{sv icon}}</ref> Rickard was born 1974 on the west coast of [[Sweden]] in [[Varberg]], county of [[Halland]] and still resides in that area.
After managing several [[Bulletin board system|BBSs]] for seven years, in 1996 he created a web community named StajlPlejsm, renamed LunarStorm at the millennium shift. The name came from his girlfriend's nickname at StajlPlejs. LunarStorm exists today in Sweden, the [[United Kingdom]] and [[Denmark]], and continues to grow.
Ericsson has appeared many times in Swedish and international press, has received numerous awards, and was appointed one of Sweden's biggest IT and telecom personalities.{{Citation needed|date=July 2010}} Rickard is also an appreciated lecturer.{{Citation needed|date=July 2010}}
In late 2006 Rickard chose to leave LunarStorm to spend his time on other projects in his own company, Bokaberg AB (http://www.bokaberg.se).
