''' Tahir Mohsan''' is the founder of Time Computers,<ref name="I">[http://www.enterprise4all.co.uk/e4all-board-members/tahir-mohsan.html Chairman of Enterprise4All 2000-2011]</ref> Supanet and Tpad, and currently{{when|date=March 2016}} manages several investment companies from his base in [[Dubai]].{{cn|date=March 2016}} Mohsan was born and educated in [[Blackburn]] and is one of five brothers. He comes from a family of [[Pakistan]]i origin, and has been one of the richest young Britons.<ref name="III"/>

In 1987, at the age of 16, he founded Time Computers, which went on to become Britain’s largest manufacturer of [[Personal computer|PC]]s,<ref name="II">[https://www.independent.co.uk/news/business/the-mystery-millionaire-1104674.html Interview with the UK Newspaper The Independent July 1999]</ref> with a turnover of over $750 million. He has retained an interest in the business to this day, having moved to Dubai in 2001 to develop the Time brand in the Middle East and South East Asia.{{cn|date=March 2016}}

Time Group continues in the [[United Kingdom]], [[Middle East]] and the [[Far East]], supplying [[computer]]s, [[notebook (computer)|notebook]]s, [[plasma screen]]s and [[TFT screen]]s around the world.{{cn|date=March 2016}}

In 1996, he was asked by the East Lancashire Training & Enterprise Council to become a non executive director, in which post he remained until 2000, when the councils were disbanded.{{cn|date=March 2016}}

Mohsan also owns the United Kingdom's fifth largest [[Internet service provider]] Supanet,<ref name="III">[https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2005/dec/02/news.business Tahir Mohsan Interview with the UK Newspaper The Guardian December 2nd 2005]</ref> currently under the control of his brother Zuber Mohsan who is the company's managing director the Mohsans family investment companies have interests in the IT and property industries<ref name="IV">[http://www.timesonline.co.uk/richlist/person/0,,34185,00.html Tahir Mohsan enters Sunday Times Rich List 2003]</ref> across Europe, the Middle East and Asia. These range from hardware [[manufacturing]] and sales to [[Internet]] services, software development and [[Voice over IP]] technology company Tpad.

In 1999 he was asked to become a non executive director of the newly founded University for Industry, chaired by Lord Dearing.{{cn|date=March 2016}} Its aim was to use the latest advances in the fields of IT to bring education to all members of the British public. Mohsan was tasked with chairing the IT subcommittee which went on to launch on time, on budget, the largest online university in the world.{{cn|date=March 2016}} In 2004, he resigned as chairman and director due to ever increasing commitments in [[Dubai]].{{cn|date=March 2016}}

In 2000, Mohsan was invited to attend [[Buckingham Palace]] by HRH [[Queen Elizabeth II]] as part of a group of young people who had achieved a great deal for their communities.{{cn|date=March 2016}} In the same year, he had bestowed on him an Honorary Fellowship from the University of Lancashire for services to industry.{{cn|date=March 2016}}

Also in 2000, he was asked by the Chairman of the East Lancashire Training and Enterprise Councils and Business Link to set up a business support agency for integrating the ethnic businesses of [[Lancashire]] into the main population.  The results was the Asian Business Federation,<ref name="V">[http://clickwalla.com/cw/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=1933&Itemid=49 Tahir Mohsan Chairman of the Asian Business Federation 2000-2011]</ref> which was launched in June 2000.

He was approached by the [[Hilton Hotels]] group to become an Independent co-opted Trustee<ref name="VI">[http://www.hilton-foundation.org.uk/trustees.htm Tahir Mohsan accepted on Hilton Board of Trustees 2002-2011]</ref> and be a resident on the Board of Trustees, which is part of the Hilton in the community scheme.

Today, as part of Enterprise4All, the ABF covers the whole North West region and continues to thrive under the chairmanship of Mohsan.{{cn|date=March 2016}}

In 2006, Mohsan set up the [[VoIP]] telephony company Tpad, which specialises in providing business telephone systems and solutions to businesses, the public sector and corporates around the world.  Tpad has its headquarters in [[Jersey]], with service centres and presence in the [[UAE]], [[India]], [[Hong Kong]], [[United States]], [[United Kingdom]] and [[Canada]].

==Awards and nominations==
In January 2014, Mohsan was nominated for the Entrepreneur of the Year award at the [[British Muslim Awards]].<ref name="asianimage">{{cite news |last= |first= |url=http://www.asianimage.co.uk/news/united_kingdom/10978079.British_Muslim_Awards_2014_winners/|title=British Muslim Awards 2014 winners|work= |location= |publisher=''Asian Image''|date=31 January 2014|accessdate=1 November 2015}}</ref>

